    "body": "### Problem\n\nI tried adding the below code to `init.lua`, but it does not work unless specifically required or sourced a second time, from within Neovim.\n\n```lua\nvim.print(\"Runs at startup, but must be required again for below to take effect\")\nvim.api.nvim_buf_attach(0, false, {\n  on_lines = function(...) end\n    vim.print('text changed')\n  end\n})\n```\n\nIs this a bug or intended somehow?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim\nifoo -- Observe that `on_lines` is not working, despite print in init.lua confirming that it ran at startup.\n:source ~/.config/nvim/init.lua\nifoo -- Observe that `on_lines` is now working.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExpected `on_lines` to work right away, without resourcing init.lua.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1569+g92d3bf101d Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1736781742 Run \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nna\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
